The State Legislature group concluded that States are focusing cell-phone legislation on younger drivers and school bus drivers.
These laws are more likely to pass and maintain their constituents support.
The cell-phone industry states that the percentage of accidents caused are very low.
Judging cell-phone law results are difficult due to the lack of clear evidence in accidents except from witnesses or driver admissions.
Driver education is a large part of cell-phone law enforcement.
A National Highway Traffic Safety Administration survey prompted the Department of Defense to restrict driver cell-phone use on military facilities.
Enforcement policies vary by military base.
